You are working on couch-kit, a TypeScript framework for local multiplayer TV party games.

Package manager: Bun (1.2.19). Never use npm/yarn/pnpm.
Build: bun run build (core must build first)
Test: bun run test
Lint: bun run lint
Typecheck: bun run typecheck

Monorepo: 5 packages under packages/ — core, client, host, cli, devtools.
core is the foundation — all other packages depend on it.

Key rules:
- Host is authoritative. Clients receive full state snapshots.
- createGameReducer wraps user reducers. Internal actions (__HYDRATE__, __PLAYER_JOINED__, etc.) are handled automatically.
- Player IDs are derived from session secrets via SHA-256.
- WebSocket port = HTTP port + 2 (default 8082).
- workspace:* references in package.json are resolved at publish time. Never change them.
- Every PR changing package source needs a changeset: bun run changeset
- Never edit CHANGELOG.md files directly.
- Never bundle react or react-native (peer dependencies).
